column1: # Name: Share of own-account workers, Total

# Definition: Share of males and females that are own-account workers. Own-account workers are those workers who, working on their own account or with one or more partners, hold the type of jobs defined as a “self-employment jobs”, and have not engaged on a continuous basis any employees to work for them.
# Source: International Labour Organization (ILO) Key Indicators of the Labour Market (KILM)
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
